  {id: 1, user_id: 2, game_id: 1, body: "You should feel free to play around on this tabletop. For example, this is where I verified each asset import and that each linked image had a transparent background.", result: nil},
  {id: 2, user_id: 2, game_id: 2, body: "Pawn to e4", result: nil},
  {id: 3, user_id: 1, game_id: 2, body: "Pawn to c5", result: nil},
  {id: 4, user_id: 2, game_id: 2, body: "Knight to f3", result: nil},
  {id: 5, user_id: 1, game_id: 2, body: "Pawn to d6", result: nil},
  {id: 6, user_id: 2, game_id: 2, body: "Pawn to d4", result: nil},
  {id: 7, user_id: 1, game_id: 2, body: "Pawn takes d4", result: nil},
  {id: 8, user_id: 2, game_id: 2, body: "Knight takes d4", result: nil},
  {id: 9, user_id: 1, game_id: 2, body: "Knight to f6", result: nil},
  {id: 10, user_id: 2, game_id: 2, body: "Knight to c3", result: nil},
  {id: 11, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "To the right is the assets toolbar. You can scroll through it or search for a token by title by typing a query into the field at the top of the bar. Dragging and dropping an image to the tabletop will place it there on the currently selected layer. ", result: nil},
  {id: 12, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Be aware that some images, particularly the maps, are rather large and may take some time to render. Their space will be occupied by a grey rectangle as a placeholder. ", result: nil},
  {id: 13, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try searching for the study map and dragging it to the board!", result: nil},
  {id: 14, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "The tabletop's toolbox is to the left. Always visible are two toggles - Layer and Mode. ", result: nil},
  {id: 15, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Mode determines whether you are drawing shapes (i.e. rectangles, for now) to the board or selecting, moving, and deleting elements. ", result: nil},
  {id: 16, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try setting the mode to select and clicking on the study map. It should be outlined in green when selected.", result: nil},
  {id: 17, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try moving it around, then hit the delete button to remove it. ", result: nil},
  {id: 18, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Change the mode to draw and drag your cursor around the map. You should be able to draw a black rectangle by placing two opposite corners. ", result: nil},
  {id: 19, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "In draw mode, you will also see at least two other toolbox options appear. Clicking the color field under \"Line Color\" will open a menu to choose a color. This will set the outline color of any shapes you draw", result: nil},
  {id: 20, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Toggling the draw mode from outline to solid will reveal a second color option for setting the fill color of any shapes you draw. ", result: nil},
  {id: 21, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try setting the draw mode to solid, picking new colors for border and fill, and drawing another rectangle.", result: nil},
  {id: 22, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "The layer toggle sets the layer you are working on. All map layer assets are rendered any token layer assets. Newly imported or drawn assets appear on the current layer. If you select an asset (remember to set the mode) and toggle the layer, the selected object will come along for the ride. ", result: nil},
  {id: 23, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try selecting the last rectangle you drew, setting the layer to map, deselecting (shortcut: Escape), and toggling back to token. If you try to select and move the rectangle, you should be unable to across layers. ", result: nil},
  {id: 24, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "As you might surmise, the chat will echo what you type into the field below when you hit enter. ", result: nil},
  {id: 25, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "There is one exception.", result: nil},
  {id: 28, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "If you start a message with \"/roll\", the server will try to evaluate what follows as if rolling dice", result: nil},
  {id: 29, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "For example, /roll d20+11 becomes...", result: nil},
  {id: 30, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "/roll d20+11", result: "[14]"},
  {id: 31, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Try typing a few messages, including a roll.", result: nil},
  {id: 32, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Note that if you want to roll many dice at once, you can provide a space-separated list of roll strings", result: nil},
  {id: 33, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "For example, /roll d20+22 d20+22 d20+22 d20+17 becomes...", result: nil},
  {id: 34, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "/roll d20+22 d20+22 d20+22 d20+17", result: "[40, 36, 34, 28]"},
  {id: 35, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "(those are actually pretty good rolls)", result: nil},
  {id: 36, user_id: 1, game_id: 3, body: "Welcome to the walkthrough! If you've interest and time to spare, I graciously invite you to scroll this chat up to the beginning and follow along as I explain the current features of the Once Upon a Table tabletop.", result: nil},
  {id: 37, user_id: 1, game_id: 4, body: "Your informant told you to meet him in this alley at midnight, but when you arrive you find only a one-eyed stranger. \"Jago couldn't make it,\" he says, walking towards you. \"Wasn't satisfied with the security arrangements. Sent me in his stead.\"", result: nil},
  {id: 38, user_id: 4, game_id: 4, body: "\"I don't like this\"", result: nil},
  {id: 39, user_id: 4, game_id: 4, body: "Can I tell if he's even close to honest? I'd like to roll Sense Motive", result: nil},
  {id: 40, user_id: 4, game_id: 4, body: "/roll d20+12", result: "[30]"},
  {id: 41, user_id: 1, game_id: 4, body: "He's way too at-ease. A revolutionary in this land should be constantly scanning his surroundings for threats. The Union's inquisitors are frighteningly good at finding such people and making sure no one else ever finds them again, and yet this man stands relaxed and loose before you, fixing you with a inappropriately peaceful glare. He's definitely up to something. ", result: nil},
  {id: 42, user_id: 11, game_id: 4, body: "If he won't check his corners I'll do it on his behalf. I roll perception to look for threats. ", result: nil},
  {id: 43, user_id: 11, game_id: 4, body: "/roll d20+13", result: "[26]"},
  {id: 44, user_id: 1, game_id: 4, body: "Scanning the rooftops, you spot two hooded figures, both watching intently. One, a man, bears a bow. The other, a woman, two thin blades. The former catches your eye and hastily nocks an arrow. ", result: nil},
  {id: 45, user_id: 12, game_id: 4, body: "Isn't this just wonderful?", result: nil},
  {id: 46, user_id: 1, game_id: 4, body: "Roll initiative. ", result: nil},
  {id: 47, user_id: 8, game_id: 5, body: "Wait a sec...", result: nil},
  {id: 48, user_id: 8, game_id: 5, body: "I ran this one before. There was never any dragon!", result: nil},
  {id: 49, user_id: 9, game_id: 5, body: "Do you always have to be such a spoil-sport?", result: nil},
  {id: 50, user_id: 5, game_id: 6, body: "Still unable to be roused from his somnambulism, your charge Kalkamedes, drawn by some unexplainable force, teeters over the side of the bridge and falls into the water.", result: nil},
  {id: 51, user_id: 15, game_id: 6, body: "Seriously?", result: nil},
  {id: 52, user_id: 15, game_id: 6, body: "Seriously?", result: nil},
  {id: 53, user_id: 15, game_id: 6, body: "We're elite Pathfinder agents, well-read and battle-forged, and we get assigned this escort mission?", result: nil},
  {id: 54, user_id: 15, game_id: 6, body: "Follow this guy as he sleepwalks for leagues to get to... what?", result: nil},
  {id: 55, user_id: 15, game_id: 6, body: "I mean, my toddler knows how to wet himself in the middle of the night, too, but he can do it WITHOUT JUMPING INTO A RIVER FIVE MILES FROM HOME", result: nil},
